wiki.summary: “Runaway” is the second single to be released from Lil Peep’s 2018 posthumous album, Come Over When You’re Sober, Pt. 2. Throughout the track, Peep talks about doing whatever it takes to escape the pain fake people cause. From his mom to lovers, nobody can stop Peep from doing what it takes to breakaway. This song was accidentally posted on Peep’s SoundCloud on June 14th, 2017, but was subsequently taken down. Its release date of November 1st would have been Lil Peep’s 22nd birthday. Read more on Last.fm.
